OL,7,F"An assessment of costs would
OL,8,Ftherefore support neither the
OL,9,Fminister's consideration of the
OL,10,Fupdated Code ` nor Parliament's
OL,11,Fscrutiny of it ` because the impacts
OL,12,Fsuch an analysis would identify will
OL,13,Fbe experienced whether or not the Code
OL,14,Fis in place.
OL,16,F"We have urged the minister to lay the
OL,17,Fupdated Code of Practice before
OL,18,FParliament as soon as possible, so
OL,19,Fthat up-to-date statutory guidance can
OL,20,Fbe made available to those who need it.
