OL,7,FNearly one in five (17%) of
OL,8,Frespondents identifying as their
OL,9,Fbiological gender (cisgender) reported
OL,10,Fbeing challenged or harassed in a
OL,11,Fgendered space. Among trans
OL,12,Frespondents, the number stood at
OL,13,Fnearly half (53%).
OL,15,FWhile many reported already adapting
OL,16,Ftheir behaviour in gendered spaces,
OL,17,FTransActual's report suggests
OL,18,Fconfrontational incidents have become
OL,19,Fmore frequent since both the Supreme
OL,20,FCourt Ruling and the non-statutory
OL,21,Finterim guidance published by the EHRC.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/17
